description.narrative: UNICEF interventions has enabled children and their mostly affected and vulnerable families access to basic and or improved water and appropriate sanitation services including in humanitarian situations and promoted appropriate hygiene behavior and practices for over 4.7 million people (52% female) with special focus on most deprived communities, including 616,633 IDPs in camps, 440,554 returnees, 93,955 Syrian refugees and 94,970 within host communities throughout conflict affected governorates in Iraq. Technical and financial support to WASH partners at federal and governorates level for construction of new and/ or improved water supply systems have contributed in improving access to safe water. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:26/12/2018
